Title: IS NOT
Description: Test a value against a boolean

Tests a value against a boolean value, where
            boolean_value can be
            TRUE, FALSE, or
            UNKNOWN.

Press CTRL+C to copy mysql> SELECT 1 IS NOT UNKNOWN, 0 IS NOT UNKNOWN, NULL IS NOT UNKNOWN;
        -> 1, 1, 0
Examples:
mysql> SELECT 1 IS NOT UNKNOWN, 0 IS NOT UNKNOWN, NULL IS NOT UNKNOWN;
        -> 1, 1, 0
